This rule provides standards for frontend components:
Follow component naming conventions
Props interface at top. Example UserPageProps
Component as named export
always separate components into separate files following the folder structure below
never create readme.md files
use arrow functions for functions and components
place helper page and componentfunctions in the hooks folder at the top level of the component folder
use snake_case for object keys,interfaces
use camelCase for function names, functionparameters,variable names and hooks
use PascalCase for component names
use kebab-case for file names

Folder structure

- features/

  - user/
    - hooks/use-user.ts
    - services/user.service.ts
    - interfaces/user.interface.ts
    - utils/user.utils.ts

- pages/
  - user/
    - hooks/use-user.ts
    - components/
      - user-card.tsx
      - user-list.tsx
      - user-form.tsx
    - pages/
      - user-page.tsx
      - user-list-page.tsx
- services/
- interfaces/
- utils/
- hooks/
- stores/
- routes/
- lib/
- config/
- constants/

Styling
Always use Tailwind and shadcn/ui for styling
always use responsive mobile first design
always use modern styled components
always optimize for dark theme mode
